pageContext.description: Typology: sub-rect. ring section - bowed faces, some irreg. facetting; five spiralled, Manufacture: intermittent grooves both on int. & ext. face - to do with manu?; longit. g.mks., some apparently in inaccessible places and pres. anc.,Condition: both terminals broken sur.'s - black brown with soil trace on one; separation of ring's poss. dam., Attached Material: chalky buff soil adhering, mainly inside
pageContext.patina: little mottled grass to milky green p.; patches flaked to light green or dark brown [...] sur.
